reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value with 80 rolls
reviews.reviewText: We are a household of two adults. During the pandemic, when people were stocking up on toilet paper and other products, I came across this deal. I figured it was easier and more cost effective, as prices rose and supply fell, to purchase in this capacity. I have found that for the two of us, we only have to reorder every 6-7 months. There are no more short runs to the store or forgetting to purchase toilet paper during our grocery shopping trips. We just stock our 2.5 bathrooms up and we are 'good to go.' Pun intended. This is a great deal though. Take a look at the shelves in the grocery stores and compare the prices. Here we have 80 rolls at .74 per roll/$59.87 per box (no tax here in PA on toilet paper). Scotts is good for our septic system and is not a thick or dusty brand toilet paper. It is the usual thin that any Scotts 1000 sheet 1-ply roll would be, but these rolls have 473 sheets on a 2-ply roll. Good enough to get the job done and they are all wrapped separately, so they aren't getting dusty or dirty sitting on the shelf or sitting under the sink.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Scott® Professional 100% Recycled Fiber Toilet Paper - A Must-Have for Vacation Rentals!
reviews.reviewText: I can't sing enough praises for the Scott® Professional 100% Recycled Fiber Standard Roll Toilet Paper. These rolls have become an essential part of my household, especially for my vacation rentals. Here's why I'm a devoted fan:Elevated Design and Quality:The 2-ply white sheets with the elevated design not only add a touch of sophistication to the bathroom but also deliver the quality and comfort that Scott is known for. The softness and durability of each sheet make it a standout choice for daily use.Environmentally Conscious Choice:The fact that these rolls are made from 100% recycled fiber aligns with my commitment to making eco-friendly choices. It's reassuring to know that I can provide a quality product for my guests while contributing to sustainability.Individually Wrapped Rolls:The individually wrapped rolls are a game-changer, especially for vacation rentals. This ensures hygiene and adds a professional touch. Guests appreciate the attention to detail, and it's one less thing for me to worry about during turnovers.Bulk Quantity:With individually wrapped rolls in a pack, I never have to worry about running out. It's the perfect bulk solution for vacation rentals or for households that go through toilet paper quickly.Convenience of Auto Delivery:Setting up auto delivery for these rolls was a game-changer. It takes the hassle out of remembering to restock, and I can trust that I'll always have a steady supply. The convenience is unmatched.Soft and Absorbent:The 2-ply construction ensures that the toilet paper is not only soft but also absorbent. It's a winning combination that provides a comfortable and effective experience for users.In conclusion, the Scott® Professional 100% Recycled Fiber Standard Roll Toilet Paper is a top-tier product that I wholeheartedly recommend. Whether for personal use or in vacation rentals, the individually wrapped rolls, combined with the quality and eco-friendly features, make these a standout choice. I'm a satisfied customer who plans to continue relying on Scott for my toilet paper needs.
